The concurrent resolution refers to the voters of the state at the
2026 general election a constitutional amendment to require voter
approval in advance for any addition to the definition of federal taxable
income for purposes of determining a taxpayer's state taxable income,
regardless of whether the state would gain revenue, or the extent to which
the state would gain revenue, due to the addition to the definition of
federal taxable income.
